{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require schools to allow children the option to retake their year next year",
        "additional_details": "Assuming that the lockdown continues into Summer, it will have cost pupils ~half of their total time in their present year.\r\nMostly, this will have little impact, but we worry that it will adversely affect the social/intellectual lives of:\r\n\r\nReception children just learning to read or add\r\nThose just integrating into new high schools or colleges\r\nThose preparing for the 11+\r\n\r\nThe cost of reducing workforce entry rate for a year is far less than that of hindering the education of a whole generation.",
        "background": "At the beginning of next year, the Government should require all schools to allow their pupils to re-take the previous school year",
